description:
In lichen_lora_l2_deinit(), the code only checks for -EAGAIN from k_thread_join():

```c
int join_ret = k_thread_join(&rx_thread_data, K_MSEC(DEINIT_JOIN_TIMEOUT_MS));
if (join_ret == -EAGAIN) {
    LOG_WRN("RX thread join timed out...");
}
```

Per Zephyr documentation, k_thread_join() can also return:
- -EBUSY: Thread is actively running and not in a terminable state
- -EDEADLK: Attempting to join self or circular deadlock
- -ESRCH: Thread doesn't exist

These errors are silently ignored, which could mask serious issues during recovery.

Impact: P2 - during error recovery, silently ignoring errors could hide serious issues. The deinit path is already in degraded mode (aborted flag set), so additional logging would help debugging.
